wsdl:operation.name: GetOrganisationSample
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Returns a data sample to demonstrate the structure of eCH-0108:organisationType. The sample contains all mapped fields. All data is fictional. </summary> <returns>Data sample</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: Search
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Search for UID-Einheiten </summary> <param name="searchParameters">Search parameters formated as eCH-0108-3-0f document.</param> <param name="maxNumberOfRecords">Number of records to be returned (max 200)</param> <param name="searchMode">Use 'Fuzzy' to receive a resultlist with a match rating. If searchMode is 'Fuzzy', only the companyname and the main addressfields are considered, all other searchParameters will be ignored. If searchMode is 'Simple' rating will always be 100.</param> <returns>List of organisations matching the provided searchParameters.</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: Create
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Create a new entry in the UID register. </summary> <param name="organisation">Data of the organisation to be stored in the UID register</param> <returns>The newly created UID entity, including the assigned UID. If UID status is "provisional" you will be informed via InfoAbo when the data has been verified.</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: Update
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Apply modifications to a UID entity </summary> <param name="organisation">UID entity to be modified.</param> <returns>The updated UID entity, including the UID status assigned in the register. If UID status is "in mutation" you will be informed via InfoAbo when the mutation has been verified.</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: Delete
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Delete a UID entity from the UID register. This will not remove the data from the register, but only set the UID status to 'deleted' </summary> <param name="organisation">UID entity to be deleted. Only the deletereason will be extracted. To report additional changes use Update method.</param> <returns>The deleted UID entity, including the UID status assigned in the register. If UID status is "in mutation" you will be informed via InfoAbo when the deletion has been verified.</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: Reactivate
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Reactive a UID entity with UID status 'deleted' </summary> <param name="uid">UID of the entity to be reactivated</param> <returns>The reactivedted UID entity, including the UID status assigned in the register. If UID status is "in reactivation" you will be informed via InfoAbo when the reactivation has been verified.</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: Register
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Register yourself as to a list of UID entities. A registration always includes a subscription to the InfoAbo of the entity. Requests with less than 100 entities are processed immediately, larger requests will be queued for background processing. The return value includes a taskId to retrieve the resulting data later on. </summary> <param name="uidList">List of UIDs to be registred to</param> <returns>Result of the registration process. Just taskId if the request is queued</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: Deregister
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Deregister from a list of UID entities. The deregistration will also delete the related InfoAbo subscription. Requests with less than 100 entities are processed immediately, larger requests will be queued for background processing. The return value includes a taskId to retrieve the resulting data later on. </summary> <param name="uidList">List of UIDs to be deregistred from</param> <returns>Result of the deregistration process. Just taskId if the request is queued</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: Subscribe
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Subscribe yourself as to the InfoAbo of a list of UID entities. Requests with less than 100 entities are processed immediately, larger requests will be queued for background processing. The return value includes a taskId to retrieve the resulting data later on. </summary> <param name="uidList">List of UIDs to be subscribed to</param> <returns>Result of the subscription process. Just taskId if the request is queued</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: Unsubscribe
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Unsubscribe from a the InfoAbo of a list of UID entities. If the InfoAbo subscription is related to a registration, unsubscribing will fail, since you must not have a registration without an InfoAbo subscription. Requests with less than 100 entities are processed immediately, larger requests will be queued for background processing. The return value includes a taskId to retrieve the resulting data later on. </summary> <param name="uidList">List of UIDs to be unsubscribed from</param> <returns>Result of the unsubscribe process. Just taskId if the request is queued</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: GetInfoAboChanges
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Get all your registered UID entities which have changed within the given period. </summary> <param name="dateFrom">Begin of requested period</param> <param name="dateTo">End of requested period</param> <returns>List of changed UID entities, grouped by uidInfoAboMessageType (refer to documentation of eCH-0116 for further information)</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: GetInfoAboMessages
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Get all your InfoAbo messages for the given period. </summary> <param name="dateFrom">Begin of requested period</param> <param name="dateTo">End of requested period</param> <returns>List of InfoAbo messages</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: GetInfoAboMessagesByType
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Get all your InfoAbo messages for the given period. </summary> <param name="dateFrom">Begin of requested period</param> <param name="dateTo">End of requested period</param> <param name="messagetypes">End of requested period</param> <returns>List of InfoAbo messages</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: GetInfoAboMessageByUUID
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Get a specific InfoAbo message by its UUID </summary> <param name="uuid">uuid of the requested message</param> <returns>A single InfoAbo message</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: GetRegisterResult
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Get the result of a Registration request </summary> <param name="taskId">Id of the requested task</param> <returns>Result of the processed Registration data</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: GetDeregisterResult
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Get the result of a Deregistration request </summary> <param name="taskId">Id of the requested task</param> <returns>Result of the processed Deregistration data</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: GetSubscribeResult
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Get the result of a Subscribe request </summary> <param name="taskId">Id of the requested task</param> <returns>Result of the processed Subscribe data</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: GetUnsubscribeResult
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Get the result of a Unsubscribe request </summary> <param name="taskId">Id of the requested task</param> <returns>Result of the processed Unsubscribe data</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: UpdateScheduled
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Pre-register a modification to be executed at the given date. </summary> <param name="organisation">UID entity data formated as eCH-0108 document</param> <param name="scheduledDate">Date when the update shall be executed</param> <returns>Information about the created task, including taskId for further reference. You will be informed via InfoAbo when the data has been processed</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: DeleteScheduled
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Pre-register a deletion to be executed at the given date. </summary> <param name="organisation">UID entity data formated as eCH-0108 document</param> <param name="scheduledDate">Date when the deletion shall be executed</param> <returns>Information about the created task, including taskId for further reference. You will be informed via InfoAbo when the data has been processed</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: RegisterScheduled
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Pre-register a list of UIDs to be registered to at the given date. </summary> <param name="uidList">List of UIDs to be registred to</param> <param name="scheduledDate">Date when the registrations shall be executed</param> <returns>Information about the created task, including taskId for further reference.</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: DeregisterScheduled
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Pre-register a list of UIDs to be deregistered from at the given date. </summary> <param name="uidList">List of UIDs to be deregistered from</param> <param name="scheduledDate">Date when the deregistrations shall be executed</param> <returns>Information about the created task, including taskId for further reference.</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: GetAllScheduldedTasks
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Get a list of all your pending scheduled tasks. </summary> <returns>List of scheduled tasks</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: GetScheduledTasksByType
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Get a list of all your pending scheduled tasks of a given type </summary> <param name="type">Type of the requested tasks</param> <returns>List of scheduled tasks</returns>

wsdl:operation.name: CancelScheduldedTask
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation: <summary> Delete a pending scheduled task. To modify a pending task please delete the existing task and create a new one </summary> <param name="taskId">Id of the task to be deleted</param> <returns>'true' if deletion was successfull. Errors are returned as faults, so don't wait for a 'false'.</returns>
